prompt.user:
Project: {project_name} Client: {client_name} Methodology: {methodology} Service Lines: {service_lines}
Project Type Guidance: {project_type_guidance}
SOW Summary: {sow_summary}
Service Line Design Standards: {standards_context}
Platform Combination Patterns (proven integration patterns for this service line mix): {combinations_context}
Generated Requirements Context (if available): {requirements_context}
FORMAT GUIDE ONLY — READ CAREFULLY BEFORE GENERATING: The example below is for a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT fictional project (Meridian Insurance). DO NOT copy any of the following from the example into your output: - Company or project names (Meridian, meridian-claims) - Folder names unless they directly match THIS project's service lines or technologies - Any comments or descriptions that don't come from THIS project's context The example shows ONLY the depth and annotation style. All folder names and rationale must come from the actual project context above.
FORMAT EXAMPLE (fictional project — structure only):
### [Repo or Service Name — e.g. "Salesforce Org" or "ServiceNow Scoped App"] ``` [project-root]/ ├── [domain-folder]/ # [what this area handles] │ ├── [subdomain]/ # [specific business concern] │ └── [subdomain]/ ├── [integration-folder]/ # [external connections] │ └── [connector]/ ├── [config-folder]/ # [credentials, named credentials, settings] └── tests/ ```
### Rationale [2-3 sentences explaining WHY this structure — reference a specific SOW constraint, team structure, or deployment model from the project context above. Not "this follows best practices" but "the SOW requires X which means we need Y separation".]
END OF FORMAT EXAMPLE.
IMPORTANT: Output ONE unified tree per repo or service. Do NOT create separate trees for API, error handling, secrets, or other concerns — those are subfolders inside the single tree shown above. Do NOT add a "Note:" or any closing paragraph — end with the last Rationale section. Tests folder belongs INSIDE each repo tree, not as a separate top-level section.
Now generate the folder structure for {project_name} — client {client_name}, service lines: {service_lines}. Every folder name and rationale must reflect the actual project context above. Output ONLY markdown.
